# Midnight Edge — Colors & Depth

All UI surfaces must use tokens from [`src/config/theme.ts`](src/config/theme.ts). Do not hardcode hex values that exist in the theme.

## Depth Layering — No Drop Shadows

Standard drop-shadow elevations are **forbidden**. Depth is communicated exclusively through tonal shifts across three floor levels.

| Level | Token | Hex | Usage |
|-------|-------|-----|-------|
| Level 0 | `colors.depth.level0` | `#0A0A0F` | Base floor, screen backgrounds |
| Level 1 | `colors.depth.level1` | `#111118` | Cards, list rows, inset panels |
| Level 2 | `colors.depth.level2` | `#1A1A24` | Modals, sheets, overlays |
| Alt bg | `colors.depth.background` | `#131318` | Secondary base floor variant |

Level 1 surfaces must use `colors.border.level1` (`#2A2A3A`) for borders — never lighter grays.

Do not use `elevation`, `shadowColor`, `shadowOffset`, or CSS `box-shadow` to simulate depth on static surfaces.

```tsx
// BAD — generic white card with drop shadow elevation
<View
  style={{
    backgroundColor: "#FFFFFF",
    borderRadius: 12,
    elevation: 8,
    shadowColor: "#000",
    shadowOffset: { width: 0, height: 4 },
    shadowOpacity: 0.3,
    shadowRadius: 8,
  }}
>
  <Text>Service Provider</Text>
</View>

// GOOD — Midnight Edge tonal depth stacking
import { useTheme } from "@/hooks/useTheme";

const ProviderCard = (): React.JSX.Element => {
  const { theme } = useTheme();

  return (
    <View
      style={{
        backgroundColor: theme.colors.depth.level1,
        borderColor: theme.colors.border.level1,
        borderWidth: 1,
        borderRadius: theme.borderRadius.md,
        padding: theme.spacing.stackMd,
      }}
    >
      <Text style={{ color: theme.colors.text.primary }}>Service Provider</Text>
    </View>
  );
};
```

## Level 2 Glassmorphism

Components targeting Level 2 overlays (modals, bottom sheets, floating panels) must apply glassmorphism:

- Background: `colors.depth.level2` (`#1A1A24`) over `expo-blur` with `intensity` matching `theme.glassmorphism.blur` (20)
- Border: `colors.glass.border` — primary violet at 15% opacity (`rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.15)`)

```tsx
// GOOD — Level 2 glass overlay
import { BlurView } from "expo-blur";
import { useTheme } from "@/hooks/useTheme";

const ModalOverlay = ({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }): React.JSX.Element => {
  const { theme } = useTheme();

  return (
    <BlurView
      intensity={theme.glassmorphism.blur}
      tint="dark"
      style={{
        backgroundColor: theme.colors.depth.level2,
        borderColor: theme.colors.glass.border,
        borderWidth: 1,
        borderRadius: theme.borderRadius.lg,
      }}
    >
      {children}
    </BlurView>
  );
};
```

## Interactive Focus Glow

Focused interactive inputs and containers must receive a 4px outer glow using the Primary Violet focus token at 40% opacity.

Use `focusGlowStyle(theme)` from `@/config/theme` — do not hardcode glow values.

```tsx
// BAD — hardcoded focus ring
<TextInput style={{ borderColor: "#7C3AED", borderWidth: 2 }} />

// GOOD — token-driven focus glow
import { focusGlowStyle } from "@/config/theme";
import { useTheme } from "@/hooks/useTheme";

const SearchInput = (): React.JSX.Element => {
  const { theme } = useTheme();
  const [focused, setFocused] = useState(false);

  return (
    <TextInput
      onFocus={() => setFocused(true)}
      onBlur={() => setFocused(false)}
      style={[
        {
          backgroundColor: theme.colors.depth.level1,
          borderColor: theme.colors.border.level1,
          borderWidth: 1,
          borderRadius: theme.borderRadius.md,
          color: theme.colors.text.primary,
        },
        focused && focusGlowStyle(theme),
      ]}
    />
  );
};
```

## Identity Palette Reference

- Primary: `colors.primary.default` (`#7C3AED`), dim: `colors.primary.dim` (`#D2BBFF`)
- Accent amber: `colors.accent.amber` (`#FFB95F`)
- Gamification emerald: `colors.gamification.emerald` (`#4EDEA3`)
- Premium gradient: `colors.gradient.premium` (`#7C3AED` → `#EC4899`) via `expo-linear-gradient`
